Description:
Our client is a shared workspace provider, offering flexible office space, coworking, virtual offices, meeting rooms and corporate venue hire to the local business community. 

 They are now seeking a B2B Sales Consultant to join their high performing Sales and Marketing team. The role will suit an enthusiastic Sales Professional interested in commercial real estate, who is ready to elevate their career to the next level. This role will provide you with the ongoing opportunity to grow your sales, leasing, communications and negotiation skills. 

 If you thrive under pressure to close deals and enjoy nurturing long term relationships with clients, this is the role for you! 

 EMPLOYEE BENEFITS INCLUDE 

 
	 Enjoy a world-class office space; 
	 A supportive and energetic team environment; 
	 Opportunity to increase your earnings with commissions; 
	 Free use of the on-site gym, showers & change rooms; 
	 Onsite cafe discount; 
	 Nearby public transport; 
	 Be part of a growing business; 
	 and career progression opportunities. 
 

 RESPONSIBILITIES OF THE MEMBERSHIPS SALES CONSULTANT INCLUDE 

 
	 Qualify and tour leads in order to sell  memberships and achieve optimal occupancy. 
	 Efficiently respond to new leads, qualify leads and book tours. 
	 Actively prospect new leads. 
	 Understand customer requirements and generate attractive proposals. 
	 Follow up, negotiate and close deals for memberships and services, including private office leasing, dedicated desk memberships, coworking and virtual office memberships. 
	 Maintain records in the CRM system in order to capture all communications, efficiently follow up and move prospects and leads through the pipeline. 
	 Meet monthly targets and personal KPIs. 
	 Maintain ongoing relationships with your clients to ensure members receive value from their memberships and identify opportunities to upsell. 
	 Efficiently attend to renewals, expansion, or relocations. 
 

 THE SUCCESSFUL CANDIDATE WILL HAVE THE FOLLOWING EXPERIENCE 

 
	 2+ Years B2B sales experience; 
	 Strong written and verbal communication skills 
	 Ability to put together attractive membership proposals; 
	 Negotiate deals and prepare agreements; 
	 Strong initiative and problem-solving skills; 
	 Ability to work both independently and as part of a team; 
	 Organised and pays attention to detail; 
	 Efficient administration skills; 
	 Experience maintaining CRM records; 
	 Commercial real estate would be highly regarded. 
 

   

 If you do not meet the selection criteria or have the necessary experience, please do not apply, or your application can be reported back to your provider, which could impact any benefits you may be currently receiving.

EY is a global professional services organisation providing advisory, assurance, tax and transaction services. We are committed to doing our part in building a better working world, to help create wider economic and social benefits today, and a strong legacy for a better tomorrow.

We are seeking Consultants and Senior Consultants to join the Financial Accounting Advisory Services – Treasury team based in Sydney. 


Key duties of the role are:

•	Support various engagements working with a wide range of clients across several industries in the areas outlined above;
•	Work on projects end-to-end, including defining strategies, solving problems and managing budgets;
•	Work effectively both autonomously and in teams;
•	Understand the evolving factors affecting our clients’ businesses and begin to develop a network of your own relationships;
•	Take ownership of, prepare and communicate high quality client deliverables; 
•	Ensure work is delivered in a timely fashion and in compliance with EY policies.


Essential skills for the role are:
•	Relevant bachelor’s degree and completed professional qualifications relevant to Finance, Risk or Treasury (e.g. CA, CFA or acceptable international equivalent);
•	Good understanding of the Financial Services industry, ideally within Australia and New Zealand;
•	Advanced business writing skills and spoken English, including excellent communication and negotiation skills;
•	Some capability in technical finance and financial risk management relevant matters and/or corporate or bank treasury functions;
•	Open to travel for work purposes, flexible with work hours to accommodate project deadlines


Ideally, you’ll also have: 
•	Knowledge of contemporary technology tools such as PowerBI, Alteryx or Tableau
•	Experience in Finance, Wealth, Compliance, Financial Risk or Corporate/Bank Treasury environment
•	3-4 years of experience in external/internal audit; 
•	Knowledge of or experience with accounting standard related to financial instruments ie: IFRS 7, IFRS 9, IFRS 13, IAS 32, IAS 39

The sponsored approver for this role is Ernst & Young Services Trust Ltd.

Regarding this role the minimum remuneration for a Consultant is $65,000 including superannuation and the minimum remuneration for a Senior Consultant is $81,400 including superannuation.

