Job Summary:
We're a leading independent CCM and ECM consulting and delivery company. We combine a passion for improving our customers' customer communications experience with deep domain expertise across multiple software platforms.

You will work as part of a passionate team of researchers, plain language experts, visual designers and technologists to analyse, build, maintain and improve templates in a number of leading CCM software solutions.
You are a software engineer/CCM developer with hands-on experience using leading CCM tools to design, develop & deploy omnichannel (Print, web/HTML, email, archive, SMS, Chat, etc.) communications. 
In this role, you should be able to identify, prioritize and execute tasks in an agile software development environment while collaborating effectively with cross-functional business and software development teams. 
You should be able to work independently with little or no supervision and be able to mentor and lead a team confidently and efficiently to deliver high-quality template development.
Our clients are disperse across Australia & New Zealand featuring well known large financial institutions. You will be able to work from home and you may reside within commuting distance to Melbourne, Sydney or Brisbane.

What you need - knowledge, skills & experience:
•	5+ years of relevant work experience as a Lead/Senior developer in any leading CCM solutions such as Quadient Inspire™, Thunderhead/SmartCOMM™ or OpenText Exstream™
•	Solid design, coding, testing and debugging skills;
•	Experience in designing and developing multi-channel (Print, web/HTML, email, archive, SMS, Fax etc.) outbound communications for batch, on-demand or interactive use cases;
•	Good understanding of XML/XSD schemas;
•	Familiarity or working experience with Cloud deployment especially, MS Azure or AWS;
•	Familiarity and understanding of the mail-house function for print-based communications;
•	Hands-on experience on modules such as Advanced Tables, Electronic Signature Integration, Dynamic Content Import, PDF Import as image, High-Volume delivery, Advanced Data Access, Output Sorting and Bundling;
•	Extensive experience in creation of Data files and mapping of Data for different file formats like XML, Columnar and Delimited data files;
•	Experience in creation of Templates, Output Queues, and different types of tables, campaigns, Paragraphs and sections;
•	Experience in Template Authoring, Forms Migration, Content Engines etc;
•	Excellent oral and written communication with the need to interact with both business and technical stakeholders directly;
•	Must be self-motivated to take on challenges and work to short deadlines
It’d be great if you also have:
•	Experience in CCM and its integration with leading financial services systems such as GuideWire & DuckCreek in Insurance, OBP/Hogan in Banking.
•	Prior knowledge or work experience in the insurance and/or banking industries.
•	Experience architecting CCM solutions for high-volume batch and on-demand enterprise multi-channel communications including print, archive, email and web delivery.
•	Experience with Atlassian Confluence & Jira;
•	Java programming experience is an added advantage;
•	Experience with Adobe Creative Suite (InDesign)

What we offer:
•	Career Advancement: Individual Career Development, coaching and mentoring
•	Comprehensive training (functional & technical): valuable professional qualification and certifications as you are exposed to new or different platforms and solutions
•	Performance Management: Goal Setting, continuous feedback and year-end appraisal. Reward & recognition for extraordinary performance
•	Culture: We are a highly transparent organisation with an open-door policy and a “challenger” culture – our motto's include “think outside the box” and “better by design”
•	Benefits: Very attractive package with bonus potential. Challenging and rewarding work environment with opportunities to become adept on new platforms and learn new skills

